(Limitations:) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (Using data from Grad Cafe sites has limitations because the data is user submitted,) Tj
T* (anonymous, which means it has not gone through a strict data collecting process. The) Tj
T* (data quality is highly likely to be poor. Submitted data may not be clean, and some) Tj
T* (fields may be missing and the naming of the university may not be consistent. Further) Tj
T* (more, applicants with waitlisted or rejected status may have little or no motication to) Tj
T* (submit data, so that it causes bias in the data.  Since it is anonymous, it is) Tj
T* (impossible to verify or correct the mistakes.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (For example, when I calculate the percentage of international students for Fall 2026,) Tj
T* (the numbers only describe the people who submitted data to Grad Café, not all) Tj
T* (applicants. Another example is that when I calculate average GPAs, a lot of records do) Tj
T* (not have GPAs available \(missing data\). The results are not reliable. Analysis results) Tj
T* (from this data can provide some insight and trend, but can not be used for scientific) Tj
T* (study or offical records due to the quality of the data.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* () Tj
T* (------------------------------------------------------------------------------------) Tj
T* (Explainations of each queries:) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (Q1: "How many entries do you have in your database who have applied for Fall 2026?") Tj
T* () Tj
T* (     "sql"= "SELECT count\(*\) FROM applicants where term = 'Fall 2026'") Tj
T* () Tj
T* (    where is used to filter the term. Count is used to count number of rows.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (    Answer: 33052) Tj
T* () Tj
T* () Tj
T* () Tj
T* (Q2: "What percentage of entries are from international students \(not American or Other\)) Tj
T* (\(to two decimal places\)?",) Tj
T* (      "sql"= """) Tj
T* (      SELECT ROUND\() Tj
T* (      100.0 * SUM\(CASE WHEN us_or_international = 'International' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END\) /) Tj
T* (      COUNT\(*\),) Tj
T* (      2) Tj
T* (      \) AS international_pct) Tj
T* (      FROM applicants;) Tj
T* (      """,) Tj
T* (    First it create binary 1/0, when it is international, the value is 1, else it is 0. The) Tj
T* (    sum up all the 1s and divided by the total number-- count\(*\).) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (   Answer: [\(Decimal\('45.22'\),\)]) Tj
T* () Tj
ET
endstream
endobj
